+### 5.1a Orchestrator code change (Decision 9)
+
+| File | Change |
+|---|---|
+| `reference/services/orchestrator/src/eden_orchestrator/cli.py` | The `--max-quiescent-iterations` validator currently rejects `< 2`; extend it to accept `0` as a sentinel meaning "never exit on quiescence". Other values < 2 (i.e., `1`) still rejected. |
+| `reference/services/orchestrator/src/eden_orchestrator/loop.py` | The `run_orchestrator_loop`'s quiescence check currently terminates on `quiescent >= max_quiescent_iterations`. Update to skip the termination branch entirely when `max == 0`: `if max_quiescent_iterations == 0: return False  # never exit`. (Other behavior unchanged.) |
+| `reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_loop.py` | New test: with `max_quiescent_iterations=0`, the loop runs through 100 zero-progress iterations without exiting. The existing tests cover `max >= 2` paths. |
+| `reference/compose/.env.example` | Compose default stays `EDEN_MAX_QUIESCENT_ITERATIONS=30` (preserves Compose's quiescence-exit lifecycle). The chart's `values.yaml` default is `0` (k8s "run forever"). |
